*Background of The Request*

As of now Confluence will not reject authentication of the users that does not have "Can-Use" permission and redirect those users to a "Not Permitted" page which is correct as authentication was successful but authorization is not.

However in a case where customer integrate Confluence against JIRA and not allowing all of their users to have access to Confluence might seems misleading for their users.

For example, if those users does not have the authorization for Confluence the administrator would like those users to be rejected and redirected back to login page with an error message such as

{quote}Sorry, you do not have access right to enter Confluence{quote}

The above feature is not possible to be achieve currently as we are unable to filter our JIRA users that Confluence will retrieve since Confluence will register each JIRA users into Confluence.

